== Simulating M dwarfs

In order to validate the method, we generate simulated M star spectra. Using the PHOENIX database, we construct multi-component spectra according to @ComponentEquation, for some input components . We then add Gaussian random noise at a given SNR (measured relative to the peak spectrum intensity), and remove data outside of a given wavelength range. We then use the method outlined below to understand to what extent the original input parameters can be retrieved.
